    "gp_section_595501561191465570": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "ac4df35c582bd3692b5cbf3a42b6589f87728c56ab633986ccd83ea0eb36cdc9_1_1_0_0__1",
        "gg5779-Q2LD_text": "<p>Here's the difference: Most “traction devices” create minimal decompression and ignore disc rehydration. SmoothSpine creates 3–7mm vertebral separation (clinical threshold) PLUS heat for nutrient absorption PLUS massage for circulation PLUS EMS for muscle support PLUS red light for inflammation. It’s not just traction. It’s a complete regeneration system.</p>",
        "ggBJa8Yn5GB_text": "Frequently Asked Questions",
        "ggGBgdMGN1b_text": "<p>Clinically effective for: herniated discs, bulging discs, degenerative disc disease, sciatica, lumbar stenosis, chronic lower back pain, pinched nerves, SI joint dysfunction. If your pain is structural spine issues (not fractures/tumors), it works. That's why we offer 90-day money-back guarantee.</p>",
        "ggJ59b-ywE__text": "<p>Most feel immediate relief. But real transformation takes consistency. 94% report major pain reduction within 14 days. Many are pain-free by week 4.</p>",
        "ggOF78_pLax_text": "<p>Yes. FDA-registered for daily home use. Unlike pills (which damage organs) or repeated injections (which weaken tissue), these therapies have zero negative side effects. Daily use accelerates healing.</p>",
        "ggZ3I5t3Bhg_text": "<p>90-day money-back guarantee. Use it for 90 days. Not thrilled? Full refund. No hassle. No restocking fees. No questions. 94% keep their device. But if you're in the 6%, you risk nothing.</p>",
        "gg_vblMSRbJ_childItem_0": "<p>How quickly will I feel results?</p>",
        "gg_vblMSRbJ_childItem_1": "<p>Is this safe to use every day?</p>",
        "gg_vblMSRbJ_childItem_2": "<p>Will this work for my specific condition?</p>",
        "gg_vblMSRbJ_childItem_3": "<p>I've tried traction devices. They didn't work.</p>",
        "gg_vblMSRbJ_childItem_4": "<p>Can I use this with metal implants or a pacemaker?</p>",
        "gg_vblMSRbJ_childItem_5": "<p>What if it doesn’t work for me?</p>",
        "ggrcqOh_tmz_text": "<p>If you have a pacemaker/defibrillator or are pregnant: don’t use EMS. Other modes are safe. For metal implants (screws, rods, fusion hardware): generally safe, but consult your surgeon first. Most approve it because it aids recovery.</p>"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-595501561191465570"
    },
